Univariate analysis revealed that TP53, CD28 or CD274 alterations were associated with worse overall survival (OS hazard ratio [HR] 2.330, 95% confidence interval [CI], 1.183-4.589; HR 3.191, 95% CI, 1.287-7.911; HR 3.301, 95% CI, 1.130-9.641, respectively) but that CCR4 alterations were associated with better OS (HR 0.286, 95% CI, 0.087- 0.933). Multivariate analysis indicated that in addition to performance status, TP53, CCR4 or CD274 alterations (HR 2.467, 95% CI, 1.197-5.085; HR 0.155, 95% CI, 0.031-0.778; HR 14.393, 95% CI, 2.437-85.005, respectively) were independently and significantly associated with OS. The present study contributes to the establishment of precision medicine using mogamulizumab in ATL patients.
