JAK3 mutations and mitochondrial apoptosis resistance in T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia.
Inhibition of JAK3 led to loss of MEK, ERK and BCL2 phosphorylation, and BH3 profiling revealed that JAK3-mutant primary T-ALL patient samples were characterized by a dependence on BCL2. Treatment of JAK3-mutant T-ALL cells with the JAK3 inhibitor tofacitinib in combination with a spectrum of conventional chemotherapeutics revealed synergy with glucocorticoids, in vitro and in vivo. These findings thus provide key insights into the molecular genetics of mitochondrial apoptosis resistance in childhood T-ALL, and a compelling rationale for a clinical trial of JAK3 inhibitors in combination with glucocorticoids for patients with JAK3-mutant T-ALL.
